---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix MICRO in Scrabble — Top 20 Highest Scoring"
  description="Master MICRO prefix words in Scrabble. Over 50 valid MICRO words including MICROBE (11pts), MICRON (10pts), MICROCHIP and more. Strategy for long prefix plays."
  keywords="micro prefix scrabble words, words starting with micro, micro scrabble, microbe scrabble, micron scrabble, long words scrabble, prefix strategy scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words with Prefix MICRO in Scrabble — Top 20 Highest Scoring",
    "description": "Master MICRO prefix words in Scrabble. Over 50 valid MICRO words including MICROBE (11pts), MICRON (10pts), and more.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-23",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-micro" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best MICRO prefix words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The highest-scoring MICRO words include MICROJOT, MICROCHIP, MICROWAX, MICROBE (11pts), MICRON (10pts), and MICROS (10pts). MICRO prefix words are excellent for bingos (7+ letters using all tiles) since MICRO itself is 5 letters — add just 2 more for the 50-point bonus." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many valid MICRO words exist in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are over 50 valid Scrabble words beginning with MICRO in the SOWPODS dictionary and slightly fewer in TWL. Common ones include MICROBE, MICRON, MICROS, MICROFILM, MICROWAVE, MICROSCOPE, and MICROCHIP. The prefix is highly productive in English." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you play MICRO by itself in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! MICRO is a valid Scrabble word on its own, scoring 9 points. It can be used as a noun (a micro, meaning something small-scale) or as a prefix. Its plural MICROS (10pts) is also valid. Playing MICRO alone and extending it on a later turn is a strong strategic option." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix MICRO in Scrabble — Top 20 Highest Scoring</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        MICRO is one of the most productive prefixes in Scrabble with over 50 valid words. At 5 letters, MICRO words easily reach bingo length (7+ tiles) for the 50-point bonus. Whether you're extending an existing MICRO on the board or playing a full-length MICRO word from your rack, this prefix opens up high-scoring possibilities that most players overlook.
      </p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid MICRO Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MICRO Base Pts</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Length</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">+2 = Bingo</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Add 2 for 50pt Bonus</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 20 MICRO Words by Score</h2>

      <p>Here are the highest-scoring MICRO prefix words. Longer words have higher base scores and bingo potential:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Tier 1: 14+ Points</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MICROWAX (22), MICROCHIP (18), MICROJOT (18), MICROFILM (16), MICROVOLT (16), MICROPYLE (16)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ Tier 2: 11-13 Points</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MICROWAVE (17), MICROCODE (14), MICROFORM (16), MICROBYTE (15), MICROBE (11), MICRODOT (13)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Tier 3: 9-10 Points</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MICRON (10), MICROS (10), MICROBAR (13), MICROSOL (12), MICROSITE (13), MICROTONE (13)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40">
          <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📋 Common Plays</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MICRO (9), MICROS (10), MICROBE (11), MICRON (10), MICROBES (12), MICRONS (11)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Playing Long MICRO Words</h2>

      <p>MICRO words excel in two situations: bingo plays from your rack and extensions of existing words on the board.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo from rack:</span> If you hold M-I-C-R-O plus two more tiles, check for valid 7-letter MICRO words. MICROBE needs just B+E with MICRO. MICRONS needs N+S. The 50-point bonus makes these plays game-changing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend existing words:</span> If MICRO is already on the board, add letters to make MICROS, MICROBE, MICRON. You score the full extended word without needing to replay the existing tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play MICRO first, extend later:</span> Drop MICRO (9pts) on your turn, then on the next turn extend to MICROBE or MICRON when you draw the right tiles. This two-turn strategy is reliable because MICRO has many valid extensions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Quick-Reference: Playable MICRO Words</h2>

      <p>All of these are valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. Memorize the shorter ones for quick plays:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MICRO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MICROS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MICRON</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MICROBE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MICRODOT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">MICROCHIP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">MICRO uses <span class="text-white font-medium">only common tiles</span> (M=3, I=1, C=3, R=1, O=1 — all worth 1-3 points each). This means you'll draw these tiles frequently. The challenge isn't finding the tiles — it's finding board space for 5+ letter words.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-multi/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix MULTI in Scrabble — Top 20 Highest Scoring</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-counter/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix COUNTER in Scrabble — Bingo Strategy</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/common-bingo-prefixes/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Prefixes: Score 50+ Bonus Points</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">�� Find all MICRO words instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
